{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VDYTzVmkTLCKSuKPRMzfCc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### Session 15 — state corruption fix #7 (2026-03-27T18:35Z)\n     4→\n     5→- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and previous session fixing this.\n     6→- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n     7→- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70, should be 74.\n     8→- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74 in both sprint-state.json and sprint-status.yaml.\n     9→- Root cause persists: ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting story statuses. This is the 7th occurrence today.\n    10→\n    11→## Token Report\n    12→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    13→- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1\n    14→- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n    15→- Redundant operations: Entire session is redundant — same state corruption fix applied for the 7th time\n    16→\n    17→### Session 14 — state corruption fix #6 (2026-03-27T18:31Z)\n    18→\n    19→- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` despite committed `done` state and proof docs in git.\n    20→- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n    21→- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70 but should be 74 (epic-16 shows storiesDone: 8 but stories still at review).\n    22→- This is the 6th time today. Same root cause: ralph state reconciliation overwrites story statuses without checking git history or proof documents.\n    23→- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74.\n    24→- All 74 stories across 17 epics are complete. No stories to execute.\n    25→\n    26→## Token Report\n    27→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    28→- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 5, Write: 1, Glob: 1\n    29→- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n    30→- Redundant operations: This entire session is redundant — same fix applied 6 times today\n    31→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"62d9d8b6-29fc-47c2-9538-fd7a78c695e2","uuid":"66d3ac7a-7c54-427b-a30d-a444afb28f99","timestamp":"2026-03-27T14:38:31.767Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 15 — state corruption fix #7 (2026-03-27T18:35Z)\n\n- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and previous session fixing this.\n- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70, should be 74.\n- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74 in both sprint-state.json and sprint-status.yaml.\n- Root cause persists: ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting story statuses. This is the 7th occurrence today.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1\n- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Entire session is redundant — same state corruption fix applied for the 7th time\n\n### Session 14 — state corruption fix #6 (2026-03-27T18:31Z)\n\n- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` despite committed `done` state and proof docs in git.\n- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70 but should be 74 (epic-16 shows storiesDone: 8 but stories still at review).\n- This is the 6th time today. Same root cause: ralph state reconciliation overwrites story statuses without checking git history or proof documents.\n- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74.\n- All 74 stories across 17 epics are complete. No stories