e it.\n\nContext: This session (session 16) found all 74 stories already done, but sprint-state.json had stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` status (despite proof docs existing and being committed). This is the 8TH time today this exact state corruption has been fixed. The root cause is ralph's state reconciliation overwriting story statuses on session start.\n\nCRITICAL: Read the session issues log FIRST. It documents this recurring corruption.\n\nCRITICAL: Run `codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis.\n\nProduce a retrospective covering:\n1. **Session summary** — no stories executed, only state corruption fix\n2. **Issues analysis** — the recurring state corruption is the #1 issue. This has happened 8 times today. Each session burns tokens fixing the same problem.\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report\n4. **What went well** — all 74 stories complete, sprint is done\n5. **What went wrong** — state reconciliation bug causing infinite loop of fix sessions\n6. **Lessons learned** — state reconciliation must check proof docs before overwriting status\n7. **Action items**:\n   - Fix now: the state reconciliation bug in ralph that keeps resetting story statuses\n   - Fix now: consider stopping ralph since the sprint is complete\n   - Backlog: add integrity check that compares proof doc existence with story status\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md. If it already exists, append with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"aa83e6495a613f543","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Session 16 retrospective appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md`.\n\nSummary of what was writte